1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:10,120
<i>The accident caused trauma</i>
<i>to parts of the brain,</i>

2
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:12,520
<i>affecting short-term memory.</i>

3
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:15,080
<i>She won't remember what just happened,</i>

4
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:18,920
<i>but her memory should gradually return.</i>

5
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:23,640
<i>As for the weakness in her arm and leg,</i>
<i>the physiotherapy will take care of it.</i>

6
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:26,520
Our love can't go on anymore.

7
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:27,840
Let's get a divorce.

8
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:33,640
<i>I've put the house up for sale.</i>

9
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:37,080
Once it's sold,
I'll pay you back immediately.

10
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:38,520
I quit.

11
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:41,760
<i>I'm moving down south with Dad.</i>
<i>Mom's going too.</i>

12
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,760
Are you really not going to visit Pie?

13
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,480
<i>Why are you hiding from her?</i>

14
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:58,520
Please, go ahead.

15
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:02,840
Come on in, ma'am.

16
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:07,440
Okay.

17
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:12,400
We've arrived.

18
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:13,960
- Alright.
- You can get out now.

19
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:15,600
After you, Miss Pie.

20
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:17,240
This is our new home.

21
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:19,800
Go ahead, Miss Pie.

22
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:24,000
- Wow, Mom! The house is so cute.
- Come on.

23
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:26,240
It's a bit small, Pie.

24
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:29,800
I didn't want to be in debt,
so I chose something just the right size.

25
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:33,600
This is more than enough, Mom.
It's so cozy.

26
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:37,840
I'm planning to start selling
made-to-order meals next week.

27
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:39,400
It'll help bring in some money
for the house.

28
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:40,400
Okay.

29
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,520
Let's go inside.

30
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,920
- I've prepared a room for you, Miss Pie.
- Thank you.

31
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:45,960
- Come on, dear.
- Please, Miss Pie.

32
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:52,000
How do you like it?

33
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:53,960
Mom, she came along too?

34
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:56,440
- Yes.
- Hello.

35
00:03:57,080 --> 00:03:59,720
Are you hungry?
I can make something for you to eat.

36
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,520
- Yes, please.
- Okay.

37
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,360
I'll help Puk in the kitchen.

38
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:05,720
- That way, we can have our meal quickly.
- Okay.

39
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:08,080
- Mom.
- Yes?

40
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:11,760
I'm…

41
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,560
I'm sorry.

42
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:26,400
I didn't mean to disappoint you with…

43
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:31,000
my divorce from Pun.

44
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:36,120
Oh, Pie. It's really okay.

45
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:39,040
I told you before,

46
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:42,760
I just want you to do
what makes you happy.

47
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:44,480
Okay?

48
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:49,320
I just want you to be yourself again.

49
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:58,880
Thank you, Mom.

50
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:27,680
I don't want you to go at all.

51
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:29,000
Can't you skip this,

52
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:30,440
that thing in France?

53
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:33,040
Mom, I have to go for work

54
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:35,840
and take a short course.
Just a short while.

55
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:39,360
A short while?
That's seven or eight months!

56
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:42,360
I think just visiting for work is enough.

57
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:44,240
You don't need to take the course.

58
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:46,480
He's been through a lot.

59
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:49,360
He needs a break,
a change of environment, you know.

60
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:52,560
Don't say anything.
Go wherever you need to go.

61
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:57,080
This is between us.
An outsider has nothing to do with it.

62
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,640
Step out for a moment.

63
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:12,000
After all the wrong you've done,
you still have the nerve to speak?

64
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:16,320
But he's been doing his best
to be with you.

65
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:18,440
He only goes to that house
a few days a month.

66
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:21,520
No matter how many days,
I can't accept it.

67
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:27,600
Mom, I'm serious.

68
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:29,920
Are you really not going to get a divorce?

69
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:33,840
Pun, what kind of son are you,
wanting me to divorce your dad?

70
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,400
I don't handle things in such an easy way.

71
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:40,600
Huh? Mom, are you talking about me?

72
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:42,320
Don't get defensive.

73
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:43,520
I haven't even mentioned your name.

74
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:45,480
I just got divorced.

75
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:50,520
I understand that you chose
to get a divorce in your married life.

76
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:52,600
But for my marriage, I'm not divorcing.

77
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,280
You have to respect that.

78
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:57,880
Your father has to face the consequences
by staying with me.

79
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:02,680
Okay, Mom. Do whatever makes you happy.

80
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:06,960
But if you ever change your mind,
I'll still be here.

81
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,200
I won't leave you.

82
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:21,480
Other men may not be trustworthy,

83
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:24,680
but you can trust your son’s word
a hundred percent.

84
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:29,400
You're saying it while packing,
promising not to leave me?

85
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:32,960
If you really mean it,
then don't go anywhere.

86
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:34,920
- Unpack your things.
- Mom.

87
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:39,280
Just this once.
I'll come back right after.

88
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:54,640
Hey, have you heard anything
about your ex-wife and the neighbor boy?

89
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:57,640
Did they make up or not?

90
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,760
Have you heard anything about Pie and Pun?

91
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:17,120
Aren't you going to contact them at all?

92
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:27,520
Every time I see Pie,
something bad happens to her.

93
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:33,360
If I see her again,
her life might get worse.

94
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:36,919
I'm just bad luck.

95
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,840
Hey, don't blame yourself like that.

96
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:42,600
Things like this can be fixed.

97
00:08:42,679 --> 00:08:44,680
I'll take you for a holy water blessing.

98
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:48,440
The Americano's ready.

99
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:49,720
Okay.

100
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,400
Hey, I'm serious.

101
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:53,200
After we finish here, we'll go right away.

102
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:55,320
Wait right here. I'm coming.

103
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:14,000
SEVERAL MONTHS LATER

104
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:16,160
- Is it okay like this?
- Perfect. It looks great.

105
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,880
Ma'am, please bring the chili fish sauce.

106
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:18,800
‪TUBTIM KITCHEN, CHEF PUK

107
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:21,840
- The fish sauce and the cutlery too.
- You're giving me too many orders!

108
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:24,440
Place it on the table, ma'am.

109
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:26,760
- I'm on it.
- Okay.

110
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:30,040
Ma'am, bring it to this table too.

111
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:35,120
- Are you done? Ma'am!
- Oh no!

112
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:37,280
Oh my! The floor's slippery from the rain.

113
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:40,200
Ma'am! what about the condiment jars?

114
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,720
Hey! You're too good at at giving orders!

115
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,120
Oh God!

116
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:51,280
Honestly, are you bossing me around
just to get revenge?

117
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:52,240
No.

118
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:55,320
Ever since you got the chef position,
you haven't stopped giving orders!

119
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:58,200
Sorry, ma'am!

120
00:09:58,280 --> 00:10:02,840
I got carried away.
I'll get it myself, okay?

121
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:05,320
I'm really sorry.

122
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:08,120
Oh my, unbelievable!

123
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:10,480
Oh!

124
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:14,320
- Pek?!
- Pek!

125
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:17,720
Yes.

126
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,320
Alright.

127
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:29,960
Welcome! What would you like to eat?

128
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:34,720
I can make anything,
but the most delicious is our <i>Rat na</i>.

129
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:38,440
Then I'll have
wide rice noodles <i>Rat na</i> with pork.

130
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:40,040
Sure!

131
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,960
But please, wait a moment.

132
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:44,880
We're not fully set up yet.
The rain just stopped.

133
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:46,880
- Just a moment.
- Should I wait here?

134
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:49,960
- Come in and wait at the table.
- Okay.

135
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,760
That's Pek!

136
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,240
Yes, thanks.

137
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:55,120
- Please have a seat first.
- Sure, thank you.

138
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,840
You can take this chair.

139
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:59,080
- It should be drier. I'll wipe it for you.
- Thank you very much.

140
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:01,320
- Pie!
- Yes!

141
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:03,320
- Come help take care of the customer.
- Yes.

142
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,680
- Go serve the drinks.
- Okay.

143
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:06,480
- Coming!
- Ma'am, hurry up!

144
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:08,040
I know!

145
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:09,760
- Pek!
- Huh?

146
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:12,680
What's wrong with you?

147
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:15,360
I'm sorry.

148
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:16,320
It's okay.

149
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:19,080
Well, what drink would you like?

150
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:21,760
I'll have a plum soda.

151
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:24,760
Plum soda, coming right up.
Please wait a moment.

152
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:25,800
- Okay.
- Alright.

153
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,520
- Taking it back with you?
- Feel free.

154
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:30,520
- Okay, thank you.
- Yes.

155
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:33,160
It's actually pretty lively here.

156
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:40,000
The plum soda is here.

157
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:41,360
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

158
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,200
Pek.

159
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:49,160
I'm sorry. Do you mind if I say something?

160
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:50,760
Sure.

161
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:56,800
Your show has helped me get through

162
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:59,520
some really tough times in my life,
many times over.

163
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:02,080
Many times?

164
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:04,000
Looks like you've been through a lot too.

165
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,160
Love seems simple at first.

166
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:11,000
But loving properly, that's a bit tricky.

167
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:13,880
Even if the world ends, zombies invade,

168
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:16,120
people still have love problems.

169
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,880
That's why my show survives.

170
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:20,920
I agree.

171
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,520
Wait, hold on a sec.

172
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,720
Yes? Is something wrong, Pek?

173
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:33,000
I forgot my wallet.

174
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:35,640
- Can I leave it with you for a moment?
- Sure.

175
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:44,640
- Hey!
- Yes?

176
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,640
Do you know double rainbow?

177
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:56,520
- Double rainbow, that's a bad omen!
- What bad omen?

178
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:59,080
A double rainbow means love.

179
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:01,920
They say if you see one,

180
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,360
people who once loved each other
will meet again.

181
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:09,320
I know it. Why are you asking?

182
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:11,440
Come here, quickly.

183
00:13:25,560 --> 00:13:26,720
Double rainbow!

184
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,440
It's beautiful.

185
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:47,000
Do you know what it means?

186
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:50,040
Yes.

187
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:55,240
Some legends say it's a bad omen.

188
00:13:56,280 --> 00:13:57,920
A sign of death.

189
00:13:59,560 --> 00:14:03,360
Other legends say it's about love.

190
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,920
They believe

191
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:13,440
people who once loved each other
will meet again.

192
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:18,800
Wow, that's spot on.

193
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:21,960
But honestly, I don't know
the real meaning either.

194
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:26,320
I just know rainbows
appear after the rain.

195
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:32,200
Let's think of it as a gift for those
who made it through the storm.

196
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:37,080
Let a rainbow be a gift, a little reward

197
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:40,120
for anyone who's been through so much.

198
00:14:46,640 --> 00:14:47,960
Thank you.

199
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:52,560
- I'll go get my wallet.
- Okay.

200
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:12,800
Why are you smiling all by yourself, Pie?

201
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:18,920
I haven't seen you smile
like this in so long.

202
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:21,120
What are you looking at?

203
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,840
- Mom.
- Yes?

204
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:31,840
I know now what truly makes me happy.

205
00:16:36,520 --> 00:16:39,240
I want to go back
to doing what brings me joy.

206
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:48,040
I'm going back to work.

207
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:53,080
Do whatever makes you happy.

208
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:55,040
- Okay?
- Yes.

209
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:58,560
What kind of work are you planning to do?

210
00:16:58,640 --> 00:16:59,800
Have you decided yet?

211
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:18,240
Here's the project handover.

212
00:17:18,319 --> 00:17:19,480
- Alright.
- Please sign.

213
00:17:24,760 --> 00:17:25,839
Job done!

214
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:30,920
Thanks a lot, Phu, for helping me
see this through to the end.

215
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,600
Oh, it's my pleasure!

216
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:36,280
When you have the museum opening,
just call me.

217
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:37,520
I'll be ready to help.

218
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:41,080
Uncle, Phu, do you have any guests
you want to invite?

219
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:44,200
Oh yes, I'll send you the list later.

220
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:47,200
By the way, I'm planning
to open it early next month.

221
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:49,160
Will Pun be back in time?

222
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:50,920
Not likely.

223
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,880
At the earliest,
it'll be the end of next month.

224
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,840
Oh, that's too bad.

225
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:58,200
And Phu, do you have any guests coming?

226
00:17:58,280 --> 00:18:02,400
I have about four
or five partner companies

227
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:05,720
and two more people I'd like to invite,

228
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:07,480
so they can see their work for themselves.

229
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:11,560
You mean Win and Pie, right?

230
00:18:14,440 --> 00:18:15,600
Mink, are you okay with this?

231
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:18,320
Of course. I was thinking the same thing.

232
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:22,520
Honestly.

233
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,600
I'm okay too.

234
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:31,840
I've let go. I don't care about others.

235
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:33,440
That's enough, everyone's on their own.

236
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:35,960
Good.

237
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:39,240
Hey, do you know
where the two of them are right now?

238
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,360
As for Win's location,

239
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:44,560
I can probably find him
since he's in the same circle.

240
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:46,160
And what about Pie?

241
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:49,080
Oh, she's probably with him.

242
00:18:50,320 --> 00:18:53,520
Honestly, Pun already agreed
to the divorce.

243
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:57,040
If they want to get back together,
it won't be surprising.

244
00:18:58,520 --> 00:19:00,360
- Such a good person!
- Of course.

245
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:06,000
Then I'll have you contact Win.

246
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:08,880
As for Pie, I know exactly who to ask.

247
00:19:12,560 --> 00:19:15,400
I'm getting married,
so I'm handing out the invitations.

248
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:19,200
Rok shared your location with me.

249
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,120
You're invited.

250
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:28,840
Congratulations.

251
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:34,800
My groom isn't Pun, by the way.

252
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:41,120
Yeah, whoever it is, I'm happy for you.

253
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:46,680
How can you be such a good person?

254
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:52,800
I've done so much to you,
and yet you genuinely congratulate me.

255
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:54,160
How is that even possible?

256
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:58,320
I've been through a lot in life.

257
00:19:59,840 --> 00:20:01,760
What you did to me…

258
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:05,480
was nothing compared to that.

259
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:06,640
I'm not holding a grudge.

260
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:12,280
Anyway, whoever you marry,

261
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:14,760
I hope you're happy.

262
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:19,520
Thanks for handing out the invitations.

263
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:24,960
I'll open it.

264
00:20:33,560 --> 00:20:34,840
I lied.

265
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:37,480
This isn't a wedding invitation.

266
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:40,960
It's actually an invitation
to my uncle's museum opening next week.

267
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:44,760
I wanted you to see your own work.

268
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:54,600
Even though I don't like you much,
but I have to respect your skills.

269
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:56,600
You're really talented.

270
00:20:57,840 --> 00:21:01,960
Even if the job wasn't completed,
my uncle loved the information

271
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,280
you left behind.

272
00:21:12,280 --> 00:21:16,040
So I wanted you to feel proud

273
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:18,760
and happy about your work.

274
00:21:31,120 --> 00:21:32,240
You know.

275
00:21:35,680 --> 00:21:39,920
More than seeing my own work…

276
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,000
is you and me…

277
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:53,560
We can talk like this.

278
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:57,880
That alone makes me so happy.

279
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:12,000
I'm leaving now.

280
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:14,680
Okay.

281
00:22:17,960 --> 00:22:18,920
Oh.

282
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:25,520
Win snuck over to see you at the hospital.

283
00:22:26,760 --> 00:22:27,680
Win.

284
00:22:28,360 --> 00:22:31,280
Please, don't tell Pun that you saw me.

285
00:22:33,880 --> 00:22:35,560
He told me not to tell you and Pun.

286
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:39,240
He really cares about you, you know.

287
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:44,920
I don't even know why I'm telling you.

288
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,200
But I want you to know

289
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:50,760
that there are still good things

290
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:53,760
in your life.

291
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:02,560
If we don't meet at the event,

292
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:07,040
I wish you all the best.

293
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:16,960
Thank you.

294
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:20,640
I'm leaving now.

295
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:37,320
Here.

296
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:40,600
Uncle Dech's museum opening.

297
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:42,680
I want to invite you.

298
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:54,200
If you're worried
about your brother, don't be.

299
00:23:54,280 --> 00:23:56,920
He's in France for work, back next month.

300
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:58,480
He won't attend.

301
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:06,200
Don't overthink it.

302
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:08,040
That's all in the past.

303
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:12,720
Everyone's fine with you and Pie coming.

304
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:16,200
After all, it's still your work.

305
00:24:17,280 --> 00:24:18,520
Invite Pie to come too.

306
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,240
You want me to invite Pie?

307
00:24:21,320 --> 00:24:23,000
Of course.

308
00:24:23,080 --> 00:24:24,680
If not you, then who would?

309
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:27,800
But I haven't talked to her at all.

310
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:30,040
Isn't she going with Pun?

311
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:31,560
Going with Pun?

312
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:34,880
How could she be going with him?

313
00:24:36,120 --> 00:24:38,200
This means you have no idea

314
00:24:39,720 --> 00:24:41,800
that they broke up a while ago?

315
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:43,960
- Broke up?
- Yeah.

316
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:46,440
They divorced.

317
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:52,600
Once Pie started getting better,
they divorced.

318
00:24:53,320 --> 00:24:56,520
But Pun still takes care of her family.

319
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:59,000
There's a lawyer handling the alimony.

320
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:02,320
But it seems that Pie and her mom
didn't want it.

321
00:25:05,960 --> 00:25:07,320
I had no idea.

322
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:12,320
Well, now you do.

323
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:17,200
Well? Did you move on yet?

324
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:21,920
You're speechless.

325
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:25,480
Your silence says you haven't, huh?

326
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:29,600
Well…

327
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:32,680
Consider this me giving you the news.

328
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:34,280
You're invited.

329
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:35,840
That's it from me.

330
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:50,120
SORINEE THAI FABRIC MUSEUM
YOU'RE INVITED

331
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:10,760
PUN

332
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:12,400
CALL

333
00:26:17,040 --> 00:26:19,360
- <i>What's up?</i>
- What time is it now?

334
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:20,760
<i>Five in the morning!</i>

335
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:23,600
<i>If this wasn't important,</i>
<i>I'd dock your salary.</i>

336
00:26:25,120 --> 00:26:26,400
It's very important.

337
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:29,800
Important enough that you should
fly back to Thailand now.

338
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:30,920
<i>What?</i>

339
00:26:41,280 --> 00:26:43,080
How's Pie doing?

340
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:45,080
Oh, she's fine now.

341
00:26:45,160 --> 00:26:46,720
Walking around just fine.

342
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:51,120
Just now, I saw the news
about the museum opening.

343
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:54,880
I even asked Puk if you attended,
because you weren't in the report,

344
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:57,280
and then you just showed up at the house.

345
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:04,000
I was there, and I was hoping to see Pie.

346
00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:06,560
She didn't go.

347
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:08,640
She just started her new job.

348
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:10,360
She's only been there a little while.

349
00:27:11,720 --> 00:27:12,920
Where is she working?

350
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:14,520
I don't even know.

351
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:16,240
When I asked, she wouldn't say.

352
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:19,760
She just said she'd let me visit
once everything settles.

353
00:27:19,840 --> 00:27:21,400
I've been waiting.

354
00:27:23,440 --> 00:27:26,520
She said she's starting a new life.

355
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:29,800
She even changed all her phone numbers.

356
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:34,880
What about her memory loss?

357
00:27:34,960 --> 00:27:36,680
Can she remember anything yet?

358
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:41,760
No matter how many times I ask,
she says she can't remember.

359
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:46,760
Well…

360
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:50,800
Have Win and Pie been in contact at all?

361
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:52,960
Oh, not at all.

362
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:56,640
But I haven't stopped him or anything.

363
00:27:56,720 --> 00:27:58,320
He just disappeared on his own.

364
00:28:00,760 --> 00:28:02,160
Ma'am!

365
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:04,080
- Yes?
- A delivery just arrived.

366
00:28:04,160 --> 00:28:06,280
Really? Who's it from?

367
00:28:06,360 --> 00:28:07,400
TUBTIM ATTWIJIT

368
00:28:07,480 --> 00:28:09,040
Pie's handwriting!

369
00:28:09,120 --> 00:28:10,840
I remember her handwriting!

370
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:12,840
Oh my, what did she send?

371
00:28:13,640 --> 00:28:14,600
Let's see.

372
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:16,440
TUBTIM ATTWIJIT

373
00:28:25,360 --> 00:28:26,480
<i>I bought this from some villagers.</i>

374
00:28:26,560 --> 00:28:29,200
<i>It looked nice, so I'm sending it to you.</i>

375
00:28:29,280 --> 00:28:31,680
<i>I'm doing fine, so don't worry.</i>

376
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:35,160
Oh, Pie.

377
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:38,280
Let's see.

378
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:44,040
Wow, the fabric is beautiful!

379
00:28:44,120 --> 00:28:48,240
Oh my, look at the pattern.
It's so stylish.

380
00:28:48,320 --> 00:28:50,640
I wonder where it was woven.

381
00:28:54,800 --> 00:28:57,240
Wait, look at her.

382
00:28:57,320 --> 00:28:59,840
She didn't even write
the sender's address.

383
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:02,320
She must be afraid I'll come find her.

384
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:06,040
Can I see the fabric?

385
00:29:06,120 --> 00:29:07,520
Of course.

386
00:29:15,840 --> 00:29:19,160
Oh, Pun, I remember now.

387
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:22,720
When Pie was looking for work, she told me

388
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:26,720
she wanted to go back
to a job that made her happy.

389
00:29:27,320 --> 00:29:29,280
It must be related to fabric.

390
00:29:47,040 --> 00:29:51,800
PUN

391
00:29:58,280 --> 00:29:59,560
Yes, Pun?

392
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:01,280
I have a task for you.

393
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:06,000
<i>If you complete it, your reward</i>

394
00:30:06,080 --> 00:30:07,880
is my forgiveness.

395
00:30:11,240 --> 00:30:12,680
<i>If you want to know, come meet me.</i>

396
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:15,680
Do you dare face me?

397
00:30:49,920 --> 00:30:51,960
Back then, I never
paid attention to the plants.

398
00:30:52,560 --> 00:30:54,800
I just saw Dad taking care of them alone.

399
00:30:56,200 --> 00:30:58,000
Sometimes I wondered

400
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:01,440
how he could spend
the whole day here by himself.

401
00:31:02,600 --> 00:31:04,720
Then I realized…

402
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:10,120
he was secretly talking on the phone
with his mistress.

403
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:13,280
I thought he loved the plants.

404
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:16,240
But once he got caught,
he never came back.

405
00:31:17,040 --> 00:31:19,360
So it fell on me
to take care of everything.

406
00:31:22,320 --> 00:31:24,520
Is this for real, or are you joking?

407
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:26,520
I don't know what to say.

408
00:31:27,280 --> 00:31:28,400
It's true.

409
00:31:29,280 --> 00:31:33,480
But at least I learned something.

410
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:36,840
Being quiet, keeping things to yourself,
not talking, not clearing the air,

411
00:31:38,560 --> 00:31:40,720
it's like planting
a time bomb in a relationship.

412
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:43,960
My dad never spoke.

413
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:46,920
He never complained to Mom,

414
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:49,960
never shared his feelings with her.

415
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:54,240
But he chose to go to someone
who could meet his needs better.

416
00:31:59,120 --> 00:32:00,600
I'm sorry about that.

417
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:04,880
It's like me and Pie.

418
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:09,480
She never spoke,
never shared her feelings,

419
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:13,000
never expressed what was bothering her.

420
00:32:14,440 --> 00:32:16,680
It was like a time bomb between us.

421
00:32:18,840 --> 00:32:20,920
And eventually, one day, it went off.

422
00:32:26,280 --> 00:32:28,640
Some things are just hard to talk about.

423
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:31,040
Yeah.

424
00:32:32,320 --> 00:32:33,640
I'm just like Mom.

425
00:32:35,680 --> 00:32:37,080
My dad didn't talk,

426
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:41,920
because no matter what he said,
she wouldn't understand or adjust.

427
00:32:48,160 --> 00:32:49,480
And Pie not telling me,

428
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:55,360
partly that's on me,
for making her afraid to speak up.

429
00:33:00,080 --> 00:33:02,280
A relationship is about two people…

430
00:33:04,280 --> 00:33:06,160
sharing responsibility for everything.

431
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:21,800
But now it's too late.

432
00:33:24,760 --> 00:33:25,720
Alright.

433
00:33:27,560 --> 00:33:28,960
Let's get back to work.

434
00:33:31,040 --> 00:33:32,520
What do you want me to do?

435
00:33:35,120 --> 00:33:37,880
Do you remember what you said to me
the last day we met?

436
00:33:40,800 --> 00:33:42,200
<i>I love Pie!</i>

437
00:33:42,280 --> 00:33:44,840
There's never been a day
I haven't thought about her.

438
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:46,960
I want to protect her.

439
00:33:47,040 --> 00:33:49,160
<i>I don't want her to be hurt again.</i>

440
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:52,280
Your task is this.

441
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:54,800
I want you to say that to Pie again.

442
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:56,560
This time, face to face.

443
00:34:02,120 --> 00:34:05,000
I know you and Pie haven't seen
each other since it all happened.

444
00:34:06,880 --> 00:34:08,199
I've talked to Aunt Saen.

445
00:34:09,159 --> 00:34:10,920
She told me everything.

446
00:34:12,040 --> 00:34:14,560
About how you worked
and saved up a million,

447
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:17,760
planning to prove yourself
to Pie and her mom.

448
00:34:20,239 --> 00:34:21,800
But you never told her.

449
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:29,560
And what you said that day,
she didn't even remember.

450
00:34:31,920 --> 00:34:33,520
Your job now

451
00:34:34,719 --> 00:34:36,679
is to tell her everything.

452
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:40,280
But…

453
00:34:40,360 --> 00:34:42,199
Things between Pie and me ended long ago.

454
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:48,719
Until now,

455
00:34:50,679 --> 00:34:52,800
you and Pie have been living for others.

456
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:02,200
It's time to follow your own heart.

457
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:13,880
I'm giving you a chance now.

458
00:35:16,520 --> 00:35:17,960
Will you give yourself one too?

459
00:35:30,520 --> 00:35:33,760
Okay, Pun. I'll take on this task.

460
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:39,760
But I don't know where she is right now.

461
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:46,720
- I don't know either.
- Huh?

462
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:03,480
But this piece of fabric
will lead you to her.

463
00:36:27,160 --> 00:36:28,440
Wow.

464
00:36:29,560 --> 00:36:34,200
This is exquisite!
So detailed and beautiful.

465
00:36:34,280 --> 00:36:36,920
Uncle, do you know where it's from?

466
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:39,400
Well, this is called

467
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:42,080
Chor Bai Makham woven fabric.

468
00:36:42,160 --> 00:36:44,480
It's the traditional fabric pattern
of Chai Nat.

469
00:36:44,560 --> 00:36:45,640
Chai Nat?

470
00:36:45,720 --> 00:36:46,960
Yes.

471
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:53,200
Pie told her mom she wanted to go back
to work with fabric again.

472
00:36:53,280 --> 00:36:58,080
When she sent it, she included a note
saying she bought it from the villagers.

473
00:36:58,720 --> 00:37:01,720
Maybe we should try contacting
the villagers who make this fabric.

474
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:04,800
Oh my! What a coincidence!

475
00:37:04,880 --> 00:37:06,760
I have a younger male friend

476
00:37:06,840 --> 00:37:09,400
who works with woven fabrics in Chai Nat.

477
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:12,000
I'll give him a call. Okay?

478
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:21,720
Hello? Is this Kachen?

479
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:23,880
Kachen, It's me, Dech.

480
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:25,760
That's right. How are you?

481
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:28,640
Quick question.

482
00:37:28,720 --> 00:37:31,520
Are you still working
with the weaving group in Chai Nat?

483
00:37:34,120 --> 00:37:35,120
NOEN KHAM, CHAI NAT

484
00:37:35,200 --> 00:37:37,720
This is the location of the villagers
Pie might be working with.

485
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:41,160
In a few days,
there's a festival about fabric.

486
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:44,600
It's possible she will be working there.

487
00:37:44,680 --> 00:37:45,600
Go check it out.

488
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:50,640
USA BOONSAPHIPHAT
NOEN KHAM, CHAI NAT

489
00:37:53,600 --> 00:37:54,720
Go!

490
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:57,000
Thank you, Pun.

491
00:38:10,040 --> 00:38:12,480
Hurry up. Go!

492
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,000
Thank you, Mink.

493
00:38:29,280 --> 00:38:32,560
I don't know whether Win and Pie
will be like tangled threads

494
00:38:32,640 --> 00:38:34,640
or threads woven together
into a beautiful pattern.

495
00:38:37,680 --> 00:38:42,560
Uncle once told me
that life is like weaving.

496
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:48,440
Each of us is a single thread,
but one thread alone can't make a pattern.

497
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:51,880
We have to intertwine with other threads.

498
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:57,120
Whether it becomes a blessing
or a consequence depends on our karma.

499
00:38:59,720 --> 00:39:03,160
<i>If they're meant to be,</i>
<i>being together will bring them happiness.</i>

500
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:06,080
<i>It will weave them together</i>
<i>into a beautiful pattern.</i>

501
00:39:07,360 --> 00:39:09,200
<i>But if they're bound by bad karma,</i>

502
00:39:09,280 --> 00:39:12,600
<i>the threads get all tangled</i>
<i>and create an ugly pattern.</i>

503
00:39:14,840 --> 00:39:17,040
I hope those two
end up as a beautiful pattern.

504
00:39:17,120 --> 00:39:18,840
I hope so too.

505
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:46,480
Did Uncle have you take this?

506
00:39:46,560 --> 00:39:48,840
No, I took it myself.

507
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:52,680
I wanted to display it at the museum.

508
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:54,200
This piece is fascinating.

509
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,520
You're into fabric now?

510
00:39:59,120 --> 00:40:03,120
Since helping Uncle with the museum,
I've grown more interested in fabrics.

511
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:05,600
I guess I've fallen in love with them.

512
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:09,160
Haven't seen you in a while.
You've grown up.

513
00:40:09,880 --> 00:40:13,040
You're not saying
I've gotten fat, are you?

514
00:40:13,840 --> 00:40:18,200
No, I mean you really look more mature.

515
00:40:18,280 --> 00:40:20,720
And have I grown up enough
to catch up to you?

516
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:32,000
I want to grow up fast,
so I can catch up to you.

517
00:40:38,280 --> 00:40:39,880
But don't worry.

518
00:40:39,960 --> 00:40:43,920
I won't pester you
or act silly like before.

519
00:40:47,600 --> 00:40:52,160
If we're really meant to be threads
woven into the same fabric,

520
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:55,080
the universe will guide us.

521
00:41:11,880 --> 00:41:13,360
- Pie!
- Pie!

522
00:41:13,440 --> 00:41:14,920
- Here.
- Wow!

523
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:17,920
We just finished weaving a new batch
of Chor Bai Makham woven fabric.

524
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:21,000
So we brought it for you
to take to the exhibition.

525
00:41:21,080 --> 00:41:22,480
- Thank you so much.
- No problem.

526
00:41:22,560 --> 00:41:23,720
It's beautiful!

527
00:41:29,600 --> 00:41:31,040
NOEN KHAM WOVEN FABRIC

528
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:36,120
LAO WIANG BAN NOEN KHAM, CHAI NAT

529
00:41:50,040 --> 00:41:51,280
Wow, a rainbow!

530
00:41:52,240 --> 00:41:53,480
- Hey!
- So pretty!

531
00:41:53,560 --> 00:41:54,760
Yeah, it really is.

532
00:41:56,040 --> 00:41:58,320
- Wow!
- What colors are there?

533
00:41:58,400 --> 00:42:00,640
- Red!
- Yellow!

534
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:02,600
- Green!
- You're making it up!

535
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:05,200
No, it really is!

536
00:42:08,400 --> 00:42:10,200
- Do you see it?
- The wind's bad here.

537
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:12,680
- Let's go play somewhere else.
- Okay!

538
00:43:16,800 --> 00:43:18,040
Hi, Pie.

539
00:43:30,080 --> 00:43:31,160
How did you get here?

540
00:43:34,160 --> 00:43:35,360
Are you surprised?

541
00:43:37,720 --> 00:43:38,760
Why are you here?

542
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:43,680
I just found out
that you and Pun divorced.

543
00:43:46,520 --> 00:43:47,600
And?

544
00:43:51,400 --> 00:43:52,880
I'm so late finding out.

545
00:43:58,920 --> 00:44:00,440
Can you finally tell me why you came?

546
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:09,640
I came following my own feelings.

547
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:15,440
This might be the only chance
I get to tell you.

548
00:44:24,160 --> 00:44:28,480
Can you remember what happened
before you fell down the stairs?

549
00:44:31,040 --> 00:44:31,920
Not yet.

550
00:44:34,360 --> 00:44:36,280
Then let me refresh your memory.

551
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:43,840
That day, I said what's been in my heart,

552
00:44:46,480 --> 00:44:48,880
what I've wanted to tell you for so long.

553
00:44:58,040 --> 00:44:59,320
I love you, Pie.

554
00:45:05,120 --> 00:45:07,120
Not a single day has passed
that I've forgotten you.

555
00:45:12,600 --> 00:45:15,760
I've lived trying to be someone
worthy of you.

556
00:45:16,720 --> 00:45:18,920
I don't want you to be hurt again.

557
00:45:23,560 --> 00:45:24,680
I'm sorry…

558
00:45:27,960 --> 00:45:31,440
for leaving you
when you needed me the most.

559
00:45:37,800 --> 00:45:39,760
I know about our child.

560
00:45:50,560 --> 00:45:52,560
I wanted to be there more than anything,

561
00:45:55,160 --> 00:45:57,400
but we can't turn back time.

562
00:46:01,200 --> 00:46:03,280
I want to use the time we have left

563
00:46:04,840 --> 00:46:06,800
to make up for the time we were apart.

564
00:46:12,480 --> 00:46:14,240
Can you give me a chance, Pie?

565
00:47:07,200 --> 00:47:08,240
<i>I love Pie!</i>

566
00:47:08,320 --> 00:47:11,040
There's never been a day
I haven't thought about her.

567
00:47:11,840 --> 00:47:13,920
The reason I went to school
and worked hard

568
00:47:15,120 --> 00:47:18,000
was to come back
as someone good enough for her.

569
00:47:18,080 --> 00:47:20,440
I regret leaving her.

570
00:47:21,080 --> 00:47:22,840
I regret that…

571
00:47:23,960 --> 00:47:25,520
I regret not knowing…

572
00:47:26,520 --> 00:47:28,560
what bad things she had to go through.

573
00:47:29,120 --> 00:47:30,600
I want to protect her.

574
00:47:30,680 --> 00:47:32,880
<i>I don't want her to be hurt again.</i>

575
00:47:36,000 --> 00:47:37,760
Almost a year has passed.

576
00:47:38,960 --> 00:47:40,640
And you can speak almost like before.

577
00:47:43,880 --> 00:47:45,200
So you weren't just making it up.

578
00:47:48,320 --> 00:47:49,280
Huh?

579
00:47:54,440 --> 00:47:56,560
My memory has been back for a while.

580
00:47:59,720 --> 00:48:02,640
I just wanted to hear it
from your mouth again, to be sure.

581
00:48:13,360 --> 00:48:15,240
Good thing I spoke from the heart.

582
00:48:16,000 --> 00:48:17,800
That's why I can still say it like before.

583
00:48:41,120 --> 00:48:42,280
Pie.

584
00:48:45,960 --> 00:48:47,760
Today I'm ready

585
00:48:49,320 --> 00:48:50,800
to take care of myself

586
00:48:52,240 --> 00:48:53,720
and care for the one I love.

587
00:48:59,640 --> 00:49:02,440
I want to start dating you all over again.

588
00:49:05,360 --> 00:49:07,040
Let's start over, Pie.

589
00:49:28,600 --> 00:49:30,520
Nice to meet you.

590
00:49:31,920 --> 00:49:34,160
Nice to meet you, Win.

591
00:49:51,920 --> 00:49:52,920
I'm Win.

592
00:49:55,360 --> 00:49:57,360
Nice to meet you, Pie.

593
00:50:48,240 --> 00:50:52,280
- <i>I love you the most, Pie!</i>
- <i>I love you the most, Win!</i>

594
00:52:47,560 --> 00:52:49,920
<i>The job assigned is done, Boss.</i>

595
00:52:50,480 --> 00:52:52,520
<i>Don't forget the payment we agreed on.</i>

596
00:52:56,480 --> 00:52:58,240
I'm divorcing you, Pie.

597
00:52:59,200 --> 00:53:01,680
Because I want you to be happy.

598
00:53:05,040 --> 00:53:08,800
<i>We should part ways</i>
<i>to keep the good feelings</i>

599
00:53:08,880 --> 00:53:10,520
<i>in our memories.</i>

600
00:53:19,640 --> 00:53:22,080
<i>How can we love without suffering?</i>

601
00:53:22,160 --> 00:53:23,880
<i>It's to love with compassion.</i>

602
00:53:24,720 --> 00:53:29,480
<i>We want them to be happy,</i>
<i>not loving just to make ourselves happy.</i>

603
00:53:30,120 --> 00:53:33,760
<i>If we love with compassion,</i>
<i>when they are happy,</i>

604
00:53:33,840 --> 00:53:35,720
<i>we are happy too.</i>

605
00:53:36,400 --> 00:53:39,240
<i>Love this way, and there's no suffering.</i>

606
00:54:13,480 --> 00:54:19,880
THE END

607
00:54:49,680 --> 00:54:54,560
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
